values
('spanish:4-2-music-tv-film-and-reading:learn:c6dcd72b', 'spanish', 'spanish:4-2-music-tv-film-and-reading', '4.2 Music, TV, Film and Reading', 'learn', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "How do I talk about the internet and technology?", "reading": "<p>Media today is mostly online. Key words for blogs, channels and devices:</p>\n            <table class=\"vocab-tbl\">\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"el blog\">el blog</span></td><td>the blog</td><td><span data-say=\"el canal\">el canal</span></td><td>the channel</td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"colgar\">colgar</span></td><td>to post/upload (online)</td><td><span data-say=\"el dispositivo\">el dispositivo</span></td><td>the device</td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"bienvenido\">bienvenido</span></td><td>welcome</td><td><span data-say=\"descargar, en línea\">descargar, en línea</span></td><td>to download, online</td></tr>\n            </table>\n            <p>Example: <span data-say=\"Bienvenidos a mi canal — hoy voy a colgar un vídeo sobre mi blog de música.\">Bienvenidos a mi canal — hoy voy a colgar un vídeo sobre mi blog de música.</span> — <em>Welcome to my channel — today I''m going to post a video about my music blog.</em></p>\n            <p><span class=\"tier-h\">H</span> <span data-say=\"Veo mis series favoritas en cualquier dispositivo, no solo en la tele.\">Veo mis series favoritas en cualquier dispositivo, no solo en la tele.</span> <span class=\"tier-h\">H</span> — <em>I watch my favourite series on any device, not just on the TV.</em></p>", "question": "What does ‘colgar un vídeo’ mean?", "options": ["to post/upload a video", "to delete a video completely", "to watch a video twice", "to hang a poster on the wall"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "colgar (online) = to post/upload. The literal meaning ‘to hang’ is why a poster-on-the-wall trap is included, but online it means upload."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:4-2-music-tv-film-and-reading:learn:3af31bb0', 'spanish', 'spanish:4-2-music-tv-film-and-reading', '4.2 Music, TV, Film and Reading', 'learn', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "Higher: deciding, using and appreciating media", "reading": "<p><span class=\"tier-h\">H</span> Choosing what to watch or listen to often needs <span data-say=\"decidir\">decidir</span> (to decide) and <span data-say=\"utilizar\">utilizar</span> (to use):</p>\n            <table class=\"vocab-tbl\">\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"decidir\">decidir</span></td><td>to decide</td><td><span data-say=\"utilizar\">utilizar</span></td><td>to use</td></tr>\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"aumentar\">aumentar</span></td><td>to increase</td><td><span data-say=\"consistir en\">consistir en</span></td><td>to consist of</td></tr>\n            </table>\n            <p>Model: <span data-say=\"Es difícil decidir qué película ver, así que utilizo una aplicación para elegir.\">Es difícil decidir qué película ver, así que utilizo una aplicación para elegir.</span> — <em>It''s hard to decide which film to watch, so I use an app to choose.</em> <span data-say=\"La audiencia de mi canal favorito aumenta cada año, y la serie consiste en diez episodios.\">La audiencia de mi canal favorito aumenta cada año, y la serie consiste en diez episodios.</span> — <em>My favourite channel''s audience increases every year, and the series consists of ten episodes.</em></p>\n            <table class=\"vocab-tbl\">\n              <tr><td><span data-say=\"tardar\">tardar</span></td><td>to take time / be a while</td><td><span data-say=\"apreciar\">apreciar</span></td><td>to appreciate</td></tr>\n            </table>\n            <p><span class=\"tier-h\">H</span> <span data-say=\"Tardo mucho en descargar canciones con este móvil, pero aprecio mucho la música clásica y el flamenco.\">Tardo mucho en descargar canciones con este móvil, pero aprecio mucho la música clásica y el flamenco.</span> <span class=\"tier-h\">H</span> — <em>I take a long time to download songs with this phone, but I really appreciate classical music and flamenco.</em></p>", "question": "What does ‘la serie consiste en diez episodios’ mean?", "options": ["the series consists of ten episodes", "the series consists of twenty seasons instead", "the series will only ever have one single episode", "the series used to consist of ten episodes long ago"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "consistir en = to consist of. The distractors swap the number/unit or shift the tense."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:4-2-music-tv-film-and-reading:misc:18c29c8c', 'spanish', 'spanish:4-2-music-tv-film-and-reading', '4.2 Music, TV, Film and Reading', 'misc', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "Misconception check", "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Me gusta las películas de acción.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Me gustan las películas de acción.</p>", "question": "Why is ‘Me gusta las películas de acción’ wrong?", "options": ["‘películas’ is plural, so it must be ‘gustan’", "the verb ‘gustar’ never changes its form no matter what follows it", "‘acción’ needs a written accent added", "the pronoun should be ‘te’ rather than ‘me’"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "gustar agrees with the plural noun that follows; plural noun → gustan."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:4-2-music-tv-film-and-reading:misc:fd81f545', 'spanish', 'spanish:4-2-music-tv-film-and-reading', '4.2 Music, TV, Film and Reading', 'misc', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "Misconception check", "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Leo el revista todos los meses.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Leo la revista todos los meses.</p>", "question": "Why is ‘el revista’ wrong?", "options": ["‘revista’ is a feminine noun, so it needs ‘la’", "‘revista’ is actually a plural noun, so it should take ‘los’ instead", "‘revista’ never takes an article", "‘el’ is only used for people, not objects"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "revista is feminine → la revista, never el revista."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:4-2-music-tv-film-and-reading:misc:052ba1b7', 'spanish', 'spanish:4-2-music-tv-film-and-reading', '4.2 Music, TV, Film and Reading', 'misc', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "Misconception check", "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Ayer veo una película con mi familia.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Ayer vi una película con mi familia.</p>", "question": "Why is ‘Ayer veo…’ wrong?", "options": ["‘ayer’ signals the past, so the verb must be preterite ‘vi’", "‘veo’ is spelt incorrectly and should be ‘veio’", "‘película’ needs a plural verb", "‘ayer’ can only ever be used together with ‘ir a’ + infinitive"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "‘ayer’ (yesterday) needs a completed past action: vi, not the present veo."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:4-2-music-tv-film-and-reading:misc:d8b30150', 'spanish', 'spanish:4-2-music-tv-film-and-reading', '4.2 Music, TV, Film and Reading', 'misc', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "Misconception check", "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Me gusta mucho los dibujos animados.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Me gustan mucho los dibujos animados.</p>", "question": "Why must it be ‘gustan’ here?", "options": ["‘los dibujos animados’ is plural", "‘dibujos’ is a feminine noun", "‘mucho’ forces the singular form", "cartoons are always described with ‘es’"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "los dibujos animados is plural, so gustar agrees: gustan, not gusta."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:4-2-music-tv-film-and-reading:misc:b9ab3da7', 'spanish', 'spanish:4-2-music-tv-film-and-reading', '4.2 Music, TV, Film and Reading', 'misc', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "Misconception check", "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> El periódico significa ‘el período de tiempo’.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> El periódico significa ‘el diario / the newspaper’.</p>", "question": "What does ‘el periódico’ actually mean?", "options": ["the newspaper", "a period of time, as you might guess", "a magazine published every week", "a school timetable"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "Classic false friend: periódico = newspaper, NOT ‘period’ (that word is período)."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:4-2-music-tv-film-and-reading:tips:c8d8ef3a', 'spanish', 'spanish:4-2-music-tv-film-and-reading', '4.2 Music, TV, Film and Reading', 'tips', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "tip — Paper 1 — Dictation (listening)", "reading": "Media sentences reuse chunks you know: ‘me gustan…’, ‘ayer vi…’, ‘toco la guitarra…’. Listen for whether the noun is singular or plural — it changes ‘gusta’ to ‘gustan’ — and whether the verb is present or preterite.", "question": "You hear ‘…gustan…’ instead of ‘…gusta…’. What does that tell you?", "options": ["the thing being liked is plural", "the sentence is definitely about the past", "the speaker dislikes the thing", "the sentence is a question"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "The -n ending of ‘gustan’ signals a plural noun (las películas, las canciones…)."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:4-2-music-tv-film-and-reading:tips:af62d065', 'spanish', 'spanish:4-2-music-tv-film-and-reading', '4.2 Music, TV, Film and Reading', 'tips', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "tip — Paper 3 — Translation into English", "reading": "Watch the false friends: ‘periódico’ = newspaper (not ‘period’), ‘revista’ = magazine (not ‘review’). Keep ‘me gustan las películas de acción’ natural: ‘I like action films’, not ‘to me they like the films of action’.", "question": "‘Prefiero leer una novela a ver la tele’ =", "options": ["I prefer reading a novel to watching TV", "I prefer watching TV to reading a novel", "I never read novels, only watch TV", "I used to prefer watching TV"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "preferir X a Y = prefer X to Y; here reading a novel is preferred over watching TV."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:4-2-music-tv-film-and-reading:tips:2f1a4fab', 'spanish', 'spanish:4-2-music-tv-film-and-reading', '4.2 Music, TV, Film and Reading', 'tips', 'mcq', 1, '{"readingTitle": "evaluate — Paper 4 — Writing & translation into Spanish", "reading": "Combine an activity, an opinion and a reason: ‘Me gustan las películas de acción porque son emocionantes.’ At Higher, add a comparison and a stronger opinion structure: ‘Prefiero…a…’, ‘Lo que más me gusta es…’.", "question": "Which answer reaches the top band?", "options": ["Me encantan las películas de ciencia ficción porque son emocionantes, pero lo que más me gusta es leer novelas", "Me gustan las películas, las series, los libros y las canciones, pero nunca digo las razones por las que de verdad me gustan", "Veo la tele y leo un libro y veo la tele otra vez sin parar nunca", "Me gusta"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "It links an opinion, a reason, and a Higher-tier structure (lo que más me gusta) — range and accuracy, not just a long list with no reasons."}'::jsonb),
